news.title: Let migration of Odisha data for PMAY-Gramin: Union education minister
news.para: Once the AWAS+ portal window is opened, data of many eligible poor families can be migrated to the permanent wait list of PMAY-G and these families can get houses, Pradhan said in a letter to his cabinet colleague.

news.title: Over 6,000 apply for 76 PMAY houses in Prayagraj
news.para: PDA has received an amount of over Rs 3 crores from the interested individuals and now applications have been sent to State Urban Development Authority (SUDA) for verification as houses will be allotted through lottery system.

news.title: Noida authority to resume farmhouse demolitions after August 15
news.para: A village-wise survey is being done through drones to collect information about illegal farmhouses and vacant land parcels on the floodplains, and it is likely to be over in the next three days, officials have said.

news.title: Akzo Nobel India's profit up 1.3% at Rs 76.9 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Its revenue from operations rose 49.7 per cent to Rs 937.7 crore during the quarter under review against Rs 626.4 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Low property tax tops PM's agenda for Niti Aayog meeting
news.para: ​The agenda for the meeting, to be chaired by Prime Minister Narendra Modi, has pointed to the dismal revenue of civic bodies and suggested an overhaul, by linking property tax to electricity or water bills.

news.title: ICICI Bank, PNB hike external benchmark based lending rates
news.para: ICICI Bank External Benchmark Lending Rate (I-EBLR) is referenced to RBI policy repo rate with a mark-up over repo rate, ICICI Bank said in a notification.

news.title: Thirteen more projects waiting to be complete under UP-RERA's rehabilitation clause
news.para: Twelve of those projects are in Noida and Ghaziabad. Another is in the state capital, Lucknow. Last month, Rera said that it had authorised the builder to finish the work in Utopia Estate housing project in Dundahera.

news.title: Jaypee Greens Kalypso Court completed under rehabilitation clause of UP-RERA
news.para: The housing society launched in 2008 has become the first real estate project to be completed under the rehabilitation clause (Section 8) of UP-Rera, which allows the regulator to take up an unfinished project and guide it to completion under its watch.

news.title: YEIDA cancels land allotted to SDS Group over non-payment of Rs 223 crore
news.para: On August 16, 2011, the Authority allotted the land in Sector 26A for a group housing project to the developer. But to date, the developer has failed to launch the project, according to YEIDA officials.

news.title: Aptus Value Housing net profit rises 62% to Rs 119 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Disbursements in the April-June period of FY23 rose by 113 per cent to Rs 525 crore as against Rs 247 crore in same period of FY22, Aptus Value Housing said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Avinash Bhosale's 12-acre Navi Mumbai plot sold to two builders for Rs 900 crore
news.para: Bhosale sold this portion to a local developer, Nitin Patel of Delta (Balaji group), for Rs 470 crore. Patel told TOI the deal was finalised some months ago.

news.title: Cement manufacturers colluded to raise prices & restrict supplies: CCI report
news.para: The investigations arm of the Competition Commission of India (CCI) has held top leadership - CEOs or Managing Directors - of Holcim units ACC and Ambuja, market leader UltraTech and 17 other firms such as Shree Cement and Dalmia Cement liable for antitrust violations.

news.title: China Evergrande to get $818 million for giving up land use rights for soccer stadium
news.para: In a filing to the Hong Kong stock exchange late Thursday, Evergrande said "the group's liquidity issue has adversely affected the development of and construction on the land" in Guangzhou.

news.title: Nashik: Forest department comes up with 2 BHK houses for personnel
news.para: While four such houses have been constructed in Surgana taluka, the remaining five will come up at Trimbakeswar and Igatpuri talukas of the district.

news.title: Vadodara civic body to enter name in land records in non-town planning schemes
news.para: VMC deducts 20-40% land from plots in the non-TP areas to ensure that it has land for various amenities and development when the TP scheme comes up.
